      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(runtime): reconcile stale running sessions",
        "body": "## Summary\n- reconcile persisted `running` session rows when no active embedded run/task remains\n- close stale rows after stuck-session recovery, incomplete assistant turns, startup recovery, and no-active-run aborts\n- deliver a neutral fallback when a native final is suppressed by the safety hook so Telegram topics are not left wedged\n\n## Root cause\nA stalled embedded run could be aborted and its lane released while the durable session row stayed `status=\"running\"`. In Telegram forum topics, the next message then saw the topic as still occupied even though there was no active in-memory run and no running task.\n\n## Validation\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/logging/diagnostic-stuck-session-recovery.integration.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/sessions.abort-agent-scope.test.ts src/agents/main-session-restart-recovery.test.ts src/agents/command/delivery.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n",
